[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### What's Done Well
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - BCQ (Batch-Constrained Q-Learning) is the correct algorithmic choice for chronic disease: conservative, stays close to observed clinician behavior, prevents recommending untested treatment combinations
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Quarterly decision interval correctly matches HbA1c measurement cadence (3-month average)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Safety constraint layer is correctly implemented as hard rule-based overrides (not learned), providing defense-in-depth
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The treatment action space is clinically appropriate and ordered by escalation level
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The reward function is multi-objective (glycemic control, hypoglycemia avoidance, treatment burden, adherence appropriateness), which correctly reflects clinical priorities
